<TITLE> Hasina visits ailing husband </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 20 (bdnews24.com)  Awami League president Sheikh Hasina went to Square Hospital on Saturday to visit her husband Dr M Wazed Miah, her press secretary said. Dr Wazed, a nuclear scientist, has been receiving treatment there since Dec. 10. Square Hospital managing director and former caretaker government adviser Tapan Chwodhury met Hasina at the hospital, press aide Abul Kalam Azad told bdnews24.com. The former prime minister, currently in the midst of her election campaign, arrived around midday to spend some time with her husband and enquire about his treatment, said Azad. Wazed Miah, under the supervision of Dr Touhiduzzaman, was showing signs of improvement, the doctor said. Security personnel were deployed around the hospital two hours ahead of the former prime minister's arrival. bd
